summary.purpose: Provides a large collection of reusable inline SVG constants, functional SVG generators, and React components for general-purpose UI elements including map markers, vehicle plate renderers, action icons, and the Google sign-in logo.
summary.problem_solved: Centralises all generic UI SVG assets so that application code can import ready-to-use JSX elements without managing raw SVG markup inline.

internal.why_used: Imports the CountryOptions enum used by the CarPlate component to select between Israeli and US plate renderers.
Imports cn (class merging) and formatCarNumber (licence plate formatting) used inside CarPlate, IlPlate, and UsPlate components.

symbols.name: CarPlate
symbols.description_one_line: Renders a vehicle licence plate component for the appropriate country (Israel or US) based on the country prop.

params.name: carNumber
params.description: Raw vehicle licence plate number string to display.

params.name: country
params.description: Country code that determines which plate renderer to use (CountryOptions.IL for Israel, otherwise US).

params.name: options
params.description: Optional styling overrides for the plate container, image, and text spans.

returns.description: Renders either IlPlate or UsPlate depending on the country value.

details.what_it_does: Acts as a smart dispatcher: when country equals CountryOptions.IL it delegates rendering to IlPlate, otherwise it delegates to UsPlate. The carNumber is automatically formatted via formatCarNumber inside the child components.
details.rendered_ui_description: Displays a styled licence plate HTML element with the formatted car number overlaid on the appropriate country-specific plate background.

minimal_correct.title: Render an Israeli licence plate

extensive_correct.title: Render a US plate with custom styling

symbols.name: IlPlate
symbols.description_one_line: Renders an Israeli-style vehicle licence plate with formatted car number and optional styling.

params.name: carNumber
params.description: Raw vehicle licence plate number string.

params.name: options
params.description: Optional styling overrides for the plate container, image filter, and text spans.

returns.description: A div containing an Israeli plate image with the formatted car number overlaid.

details.what_it_does: Renders a div with class car_plate _car_plate. Inside it places an img tag pointing to /images/car_plate.png (styled via options.filter) and a span containing the car number formatted by formatCarNumber. Accepts optional className, style, spanContainerClassName, and spanClassName overrides via the options prop.
details.rendered_ui_description: Displays an Israeli vehicle licence plate background image with the hyphen-formatted car number text overlaid on top.

symbols.name: UsPlate
symbols.description_one_line: Renders a US-style vehicle licence plate with formatted car number and optional styling.

params.name: carNumber
params.description: Raw vehicle licence plate number string.

params.name: options
params.description: Optional styling overrides for the plate container and text spans.

returns.description: A div styled as a US plate with grey background and the formatted car number.

details.what_it_does: Renders a div with class car_plate _car_plate containing a grey-background container (bg-[#b9bebe]) with a dark blue span (text-[#102246]) displaying the hyphen-formatted car number. Accepts optional className, style, spanContainerClassName, and spanClassName overrides via the options prop.
details.rendered_ui_description: Displays a US-style vehicle licence plate with a grey background and dark blue car number text.

symbols.name: GoogleSvgProps
symbols.description_one_line: Props interface for the GoogleSvg component defining optional width, height, and viewBox attributes.

details.what_it_does: Defines the optional props accepted by the GoogleSvg component. All three fields are optional; GoogleSvg uses its own defaults when they are omitted.

minimal_correct.title: Typing GoogleSvg props
minimal_correct.code:
import type { GoogleSvgProps } from 'akeyless-assets-commons';

const props: GoogleSvgProps = { width: '32px', height: '32px' };

symbols.name: GoogleSvg
symbols.description_one_line: Renders the Google multi-colour logo SVG with configurable dimensions and viewBox.

params.name: width
params.description: Width of the SVG element. Defaults to '20px'.

params.name: height
params.description: Height of the SVG element. Defaults to '20px'.

returns.description: An SVG element depicting the Google G logo in its four brand colours (blue, green, yellow, red).

details.what_it_does: Renders the official Google multi-colour logo SVG using four path elements, each filled with one of the four Google brand colours. Accepts optional width, height, and viewBox props for flexible sizing. Used in sign-in-with-Google buttons.
details.rendered_ui_description: Displays the well-known Google G logo icon in blue, green, yellow, and red.

extensive_correct.title: Render with custom size in a sign-in button
extensive_correct.code:
import { GoogleSvg } from 'akeyless-assets-commons';

<button className="google-signin-btn">
  <GoogleSvg width="24px" height="24px" />
  Sign in with Google
</button>

known_gaps: Several mid-file SVG constants (garegeModSvg, asteriskSvg, deleteSvg, tripsSvg, cameraSvg, videoHistorySvg, carCardSvg, infoSvg, infoSvg2, redXSvg, greenVSvg, garbageSvg, editSvg, addPolygonSvg, circlePolygonSvg, freeShapePolygonSvg, circleDefaultPolygonSvg, freeShapeDefaultPolygonSvg, phoneSvg, userSvg, xSvg, shrinkScrenSvg, passwordSvg, alertSvg, mapSvg, polygonSvg, carSvg, carCutSvg, carSvg2, glassSvg, akeylessLogoSvg, menuSvg) are documented at the constant level. Line ranges are approximate due to the large file size; exact boundaries may be off by a few lines.
